subSubSection.paragraph:
The numerous descriptions of new 

Orthotrichum

species within the last three decades indicate that 

Orthotrichum

is a genus which has not been studied extensively enough in former times. Nevertheless, it is surprising that such a distinctive species as 

O. dentatum

has previously been overlooked in a well-studied area (see 
Mari, 1894
; 
Limpricht, 1895
; 
Culmann, 1915
; 
Mönkemeyer, 1927
; 
Jäggli, 1933
, 
1950
; 
Düll, 1991
; 
Cortini Pedrotti & Lara, 2001
).
